reviews.review_text:
It's Not So Bad "Because it's not the meat," she said, "It 's the motion of the ocean." And a very well recorded Front-Of-Board version by Barry, BTW.  Richie's 1st set capture in the other upload is brighter and punchier, being in the 6th row, but this is the one to have for the 2nd.

For my own personal taste, I decided to start the 2nd set file with He's Gone > Jam with the jam being quite good.  Tossed out Drums and Space and faded in a solid Wharf Rat to the jam.  If you splice it right, it makes for a wonderful transition.  Then added China Cat > IKYR after WR.  That was a little trickier since the outro and intro were so short.  But I like the flow and it ends the set nicely.

I wouldn't throw the show out of bed for eating crackers.  Yes, it's average but, ahhh, what an average!  I'll take an average, 6th and 14th row FOB show recorded well to a super show with a horribly sterile and vocally hot and tinny SBD any day.  The ambient sound is perfect!  It's so refreshing not to have to mess with the sliders subtracting or adding bass, treble, or reverb - which is usually S.O.P. for me.  Thanks Barry!
